I thought the article was rubblish - for the following reasons:So we have an anti-NG article, aimed at supporting the idiot Adonis (remind me about his track record in education & his support for the dark lord aka Blair). Had the writer had any professional contact with NG then clap trap such as " National Grid, too, is stuck in the past and frightened of the future" would not have been written. NG only balances supply & demand in a half hour time frame - that is what it has done since the T-vermins decided it was a good idea to privatise generation and network monopolies. If you operate a transmission network you HAVE to maintain network stability - and that means balancing supply and demand - operationally over some period of time. The cut-off between markets and operations is set at 30 mins - it could be 15 mins. The NIC is a bunch of place men with Adonis at its head. The report is a pile of shite & whilst trying to undermine NG (and fails to find my support for its break up) never gets to grips with the DNOs, DECC and Ofgem - the real villains of the piece.Adonis would not know a "better managed network" if it fell on him - he was seen by the T-vermins and the towel folder as a safe pair of hands & sure enough he has delivered. In the case of demand flexibility - the reason the Uk has done badly is purely down to DECC (run by that brainless tart Amber Dudd) and Ofgem - who have consistently failed to regulate the big six. Oddly, NG is doing something about demand response - but you would not think that from the article.Re-nationalise the networks.Tell NG & the DNOs that their rationale is:a reliable supply, support for the more effective use of electricity, support for more embedded generation & the socialisation of network costs to support that, abolition of Ofgem, bring back the Eleectiricty Council. There - done.



