Germany could reduce their CO2 output further by closing a few coal fired power stations. They are net exporters of electricity to Switzerland, Netherlands, Austria and Luxembourg. Their electricity exports have now risen to 10% of their production. CO2 output in Germany fell to its lowest point in 2014 at 902 million tons equiv., down from 1248 million tons equiv. in 1990. Their target is 749 million tons equiv. in 2020 and 562 million tons equiv. in 2030.



